But this I muſt pronounce with Ignatius. Whoſoever doth call 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 ,Ignatius epiſt. 6. ad Philadelph. that is, marriage impure, or meates impious;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 : ſuch an one is wrought by the Devill, to fall from the faith. Or yet more plainly with Saint Paul: Whoſoever doth prohibere, forbid (that is, by a Law reſtraine) meates, and marriage, ſuch doe teach the doctrine of Devils. Now how I ſhould free theſe Doctrines, Devils, Satan, and Apoſtafie from the Church of
Rome; This is that, which ſurpaſſeth my underſtanding.
